headline: Brown & Brown Gets Downgraded But Analyst Still Vouches For Long-Term Growth
summary: Morgan Stanley analyst Bob Jian Huang downgraded Brown & Brown, Inc. (NYSE:BRO) to Equal-weight from Overweight and maintained a price forecast of $128. The analyst writes that while he remains confident in Brown & Brown's long-term growth and margin potential, the strong year-to-date stock performance limits its attractiveness.
